  <channel>
    <title>Syria contributor: DR. Ahmad Tarakji</title>
    <description>Dr. Ahmad Tarakji is the president of the Syrian American Medical Society and also a current board member of the SAMS Foundation. Dr. Tarakji is a cardiothoracic surgeon in California, and a former clinical assistant professor at Stanford University. At SAMS, he spearheads and participates in numerous initiatives, including providing trauma and critical care courses for Syrian physicians and nurses, overseeing SAMS’s advocacy work, and chairing previous SAMS international and national conferences.
</description>
